<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0c9fc012-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s804"><num value="804">§ 804.</num><heading> Limitation on grants to any one State</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Not more than 10 per centum of the total amount appropriated for the purposes of this chapter may be used for making grants to any one State.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id0c9fc013-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/88/560/tVII/s805">Pub. L. 88–560, title VII, § 805</ref>, formerly § 804, <date date="1964-09-02">Sept. 2, 1964</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/78/803">78 Stat. 803</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/90/19/s21/d">Pub. L. 90–19, § 21(d)</ref>, <date date="1967-05-25">May 25, 1967</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/81/26">81 Stat. 26</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/91/152/tIII/s307">Pub. L. 91–152, title III, § 307</ref>, <date date="1969-12-24">Dec. 24, 1969</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/83/394">83 Stat. 394</ref>; renumbered § 805, <ref href="/us/pl/93/383/tIV/s402/c/1">Pub. L. 93–383, title IV, § 402(c)(1)</ref>, <date date="1974-08-22">Aug. 22, 1974</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/88/692">88 Stat. 692</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id0c9fc014-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id0c9fc015-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id0c9fc016-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1969—<ref href="/us/pl/91/152">Pub. L. 91–152</ref> substituted provisions that not more than 10 per centum of the total amount appropriated be used for making grants to any one State for provisions that authorized the Secretary to provide technical assistance, etc., to State and local bodies. The former provisions of the section are now set forth in <ref href="/us/usc/t20/s805">section 805 of this title</ref> with minor amendments.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1967—<ref href="/us/pl/90/19">Pub. L. 90–19</ref> substituted “Secretary” for “Administrator” wherever appearing.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
